We recommended that the Local Chief Executive to:

Direct the officers and employees concerned  to  liquidate immediately their outstanding  cash advances by:

issuing demand letters to concerned officials and personnel for the immediate settlement of the other cash advances that remained unliquidated for more than 30 days; and

demanding the immediate refund of excess claims for travel and other claims.  Otherwise, withhold any money due them and settle their obligations as authorized under Sec. 37 of PD 1445; 

Stop the granting of cash advances other than traveling expenses to elected officials and to any purpose to non-permanent employee of the Municipality;

Discontinue the practice of allowing cash advance other than traveling expense to non-bonded employee;

Strengthen the operation of preventive and monitoring controls to ensure timely submission of liquidation documents and full accounting of balances of cash advances for travel by;

monitoring strictly the period of liquidating cash advances for travel which shall be within sixty (60) days after return to the Philippines, in case of foreign travel or within thirty (30) days after return to permanent official station in the case of local travel, as provided by COA Circular No. 97-002; and

Impose sanctions, if appropriate, to ensure collections of the same.  Henceforth, provisions of COA Circular No. 97-002 be strictly observed.

We recommended that Management in order to avoid possible issuance of Notice of Suspension or Disallowance for future transactions to:

Require the Bids and Awards Committee to indicate the Approved Budget for the Contract in the Request for Quotation form;

Send invitation/ communication and confirmation to/from the concerned participants of trainings and conferences; 

Observe economy and austerity measures on catering services during conferences and consultative meetings among constituents; 

Require the Municipal Accountant to secure certification from BAC that bidder’s business permit and other documents is in their file already and attached the same in the disbursement voucher; and

Expenses for meals and snacks of visitors be charged to the Representation Allowance of the concerned Municipal Official.

